 url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/_YNX1321-2.jpg"><media:title>Ty Watters at 2026 NCAA Wrestling Championships</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/_YNX1321-2.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 21:26:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>18</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58910</s:story_id></item><item><title>Program Record Crowd Packs Coliseum, WVU Advances to NCAA Second Round</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/womens-basketball-program-record-crowd-packs-coliseum-wvu-advances-to-ncaa-second-round</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/womens-basketball-program-record-crowd-packs-coliseum-wvu-advances-to-ncaa-second-round</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Celia Riviere" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/21/Untitled-2.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 4-seeded West Virginia women's basketball team collected a win in the NCAA First Round for the third straight season, in front of a program record 13,504 fans inside Hope Coliseum. WVU raced past No. 13 Miami 82-54, as the 28-point win is the largest margin of victory in an NCAA Tournament game in program history.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/Untitled-2.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/Untitled-2.jpg"><media:title>Celia Riviere</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/Untitled-2.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 20:56:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58908</s:story_id></item><item><title>Moura, McDonald Post Wins as WVU Splits Weekend Meets</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/track-field-moura-mcdonald-post-wins-as-wvu-splits-weekend-meets</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/track-field-moura-mcdonald-post-wins-as-wvu-splits-weekend-meets</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tatiana Moura" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/21/JLS_6810__1_.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia split squads over the weekend, competing at the Marty Pushkin Invitational in Morgantown and the USF Alumni Invitational in Tampa.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/JLS_6810__1_.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/JLS_6810__1_.jpg"><media:title>Tatiana Moura</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/21/JLS_6810__1_.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 20:37:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58907</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Finish Competition at 2026 Big 12 Championship</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/gymnastics-mountaineers-finish-competition-at-2026-big-12-championship</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/21/gymnastics-mountaineers-finish-competition-at-2026-big-12-championship</guid><category>Gymnastics</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="emerson smith" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_han